---
description: Git and docs must not credit Cursor or similar tools as co-authors
alwaysApply: true
---

# Contributor attribution

- Do **not** add `Co-authored-by:` trailers (or similar) for Cursor, Copilot, or other AI assistants.
- Do **not** add `Made-with:` / `Made with Cursor` trailers, or any other tool-attribution `git commit --trailer` lines.
- Do **not** add “Made with Cursor” badges or equivalent tool marketing to README, docs, or commit message bodies.

Human contributors use normal Git author/committer fields only, unless the maintainer explicitly requests otherwise.

When using Cursor’s terminal or agent to run `git commit`, **omit** `--trailer` arguments entirely for this repository.
